# The `XRayFileHeader` Struct Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

XRay traces all have a header providing some top-matter information useful to help tools determine how to interpret the information available in the trace. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

XRay traces all have a header providing some top-matter information useful to help tools determine how to interpret the information available in the trace.

Definition at line 27 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/xray/xrayrecord-h">XRayRecord.h</a>.

### CycleFrequency {#a339e015c9be8d198e2920293112f2d9a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>uint64&#95;t llvm::xray::XRayFileHeader::CycleFrequency = 0</>}>
The number of cycles per second for the CPU that produced the timestamp counter (TSC) values.

Useful for estimating the amount of time that elapsed between two TSCs on some platforms.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/xray/xrayrecord-h/#l00045">45</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/xray/xrayrecord-h">XRayRecord.h</a>.
